cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing and provisioning MapReduce applications in a cluster environment. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper studies the network load of MapReduce applications. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes an analytical method to model the dependency between configuration parameters and network load. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.PF (Performance) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper may touch upon security and performance issues related to MapReduce applications.
